WEBVTT


00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:02.880
The three US states with the best healthcare system

00:00:02.880 --> 00:00:04.240
No. 3 Minnesota.

00:00:04.240 --> 00:00:06.080
With approximately 94%

00:00:06.080 --> 00:00:08.500
of its population covered by health insurance,

00:00:08.560 --> 00:00:10.000
Minnesota stands out for its

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.440
robust healthcare infrastructure and initiatives.

00:00:12.440 --> 00:00:15.160
The state consistently ranks high in health outcomes

00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:16.240
and access to care

00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:18.960
due to its extensive network of healthcare providers

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:21.080
and emphasis on preventive services.

00:00:21.080 --> 00:00:22.160
No.2 Hawaii

00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:23.440
this island paradise

00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:27.200
boasts an impressively low uninsured rate of around 4%,

00:00:27.200 --> 00:00:28.120
primarily due to

00:00:28.120 --> 00:00:30.480
the state's employer based health insurance system.

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:32.760
Hawaii's unique Prepaid Healthcare Act

00:00:32.760 --> 00:00:35.320
mandates that employers provide health insurance to

00:00:35.320 --> 00:00:37.720
employees working over 20 hours per week,

00:00:37.720 --> 00:00:39.360
ensuring widespread coverage.

00:00:39.360 --> 00:00:41.080
Before revealing the number one,

00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:43.360
remember to subscribe and like the video.

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:45.180
No. 1 Massachusetts

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:47.280
known for its top notch healthcare system,

00:00:47.280 --> 00:00:48.480
boasting one of the highest

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:50.400
rates of insured residents in the nation

00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:52.240
at around 97%.

00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:54.560
The state's Innovative Healthcare Reform,

00:00:54.560 --> 00:00:57.800
including the landmark 2006 health insurance mandate,

00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:00.280
drastically reduced the uninsured rate

00:01:00.280 --> 00:01:02.120
and increased access to care.

00:01:02.120 --> 00:01:04.280
And you, do you live in one of these states

00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:05.480
and do you agree to this?

